{"by":"yason","id":47764093,"kids":[47764789],"parent":47752819,"text":"Why make C-a your prefix key? Just because it&#x27;s the default in &#x27;screen&#x27;? I use C-a a lot to go to BOL, just like C-e to go to EOL. I also use C-b a lot with C-f.<p>The obvious choice is C-z.<p>You rarely suspend processes and when you do, C-zC-z is pretty quick. For other combos, it pays to have control and z close to each other so that when your little finger and ring finger operate C-z then your other fingers can freely type whatever follows the prefix without having to unwind your fingers back from the keyboard first.","time":1776165523,"type":"comment"}